00:00:00.390 --> 00:00:02.930
So as a startup, when you want to

00:00:02.930 --> 00:00:07.760
implement an incentive plan into your
marketing plan, what do you need to do?

00:00:07.760 --> 00:00:11.340
So first of all, like everything,
it has to make sense.

00:00:11.340 --> 00:00:14.750
Your offering should be
part of your product,

00:00:14.750 --> 00:00:18.660
which means that your offering
should make sense to you and

00:00:18.660 --> 00:00:21.380
you need to encourage something
that you want your users to do.

00:00:22.510 --> 00:00:25.570
You want the offering to be precise for
your users,

00:00:25.570 --> 00:00:27.730
is something that offer money.

00:00:27.730 --> 00:00:31.040
It doesn't have to be money,
it can also be virtual coins.

00:00:31.040 --> 00:00:34.320
Let's say that I'm promoting
a virtual game, and

00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:35.650
if you're going to invite your friends.

00:00:35.650 --> 00:00:37.770
I'm going to give you 50 coins.

00:00:37.770 --> 00:00:38.560
Okay.

00:00:38.560 --> 00:00:41.220
I don't care about it, but
my users care about it, and

00:00:41.220 --> 00:00:43.540
they will eventually,
hopefully pay for it.

00:00:43.540 --> 00:00:45.520
So they think this is a good thing.

00:00:45.520 --> 00:00:49.130
So a few examples about how to
create great promotional plans.

00:00:49.130 --> 00:00:51.860
First of all PayPal,
they probably created the first and

00:00:51.860 --> 00:00:53.918
most famous promotional plans for
start ups.

00:00:53.918 --> 00:00:59.340
They basically paid the users to open
an account and invite someone else.

00:00:59.340 --> 00:01:03.320
Thinking the target was if you
open an account you get ten bucks

00:01:03.320 --> 00:01:05.530
into your account,
do whatever you want with it.

00:01:05.530 --> 00:01:08.010
If you're inviting someone else,
you're getting ten bucks and

00:01:08.010 --> 00:01:09.760
he's getting ten bucks.

00:01:09.760 --> 00:01:14.070
And that helped them to go to about
100 million users in a very fast way.

00:01:14.070 --> 00:01:18.730
They obviously didn't pay so
much money for so many people, they

00:01:18.730 --> 00:01:23.250
reduced it gradually from five bucks
to one buck, eventually to nothing.

00:01:23.250 --> 00:01:26.630
But that really helped
them go significantly.

00:01:26.630 --> 00:01:31.220
Another example that people may know
even better is the Dropbox example.

00:01:31.220 --> 00:01:34.680
They gave a lot of storage to their
users who invite other peoples so

00:01:34.680 --> 00:01:40.440
you could get a free account basically
of up to 12 gigs of free storage room.

