But that was huge and
people was competing each other.

00:01:52.800 --> 00:01:57.030
Who will get to their friends faster,
know to invite them and

00:01:57.030 --> 00:02:00.390
make sure that they will
accept the invitation.

00:02:00.390 --> 00:02:04.500
And both examples the people in
DropBox makes perfect sense.

00:02:04.500 --> 00:02:07.270
People, it's all about the money, you're
getting the money in your account,

00:02:07.270 --> 00:02:09.270
you can do whatever you want with it.

00:02:09.270 --> 00:02:11.750
And you can use it to buy on eBay for

00:02:11.750 --> 00:02:15.480
example, that was the best source
of growth back in the day.

00:02:15.480 --> 00:02:17.380
And for Dropbox.

00:02:17.380 --> 00:02:18.510
We're a storage company.

00:02:18.510 --> 00:02:20.030
You're getting free storage.

00:02:20.030 --> 00:02:21.280
Invite your friends.

00:02:21.280 --> 00:02:23.750
That had them grow to so many users,

00:02:23.750 --> 00:02:28.230
and people are still trying to
imitate those promotional trends.

00:02:28.230 --> 00:02:29.960
Another example is Zynga.

00:02:29.960 --> 00:02:31.250
When you're inviting your friends,

00:02:31.250 --> 00:02:34.760
you're getting virtual currency for
to see the games that they're promoting.

