00:04:09.730 --> 00:04:11.400
As you grow, as you become more and

00:04:11.400 --> 00:04:14.870
more successful,
people take advantage of that.

00:04:14.870 --> 00:04:16.320
The math doesn't make sense anymore.

00:04:17.760 --> 00:04:19.990
It was working for paper.

00:04:19.990 --> 00:04:23.190
But as you're growing more and
more users, you don't want to do it

00:04:23.190 --> 00:04:26.550
anymore because you want to encourage
them to actually pay for that data.

00:04:26.550 --> 00:04:30.990
You don't want to make them dependent
on your specific dynamics and

00:04:30.990 --> 00:04:33.600
mechanics for earning virtual currency.

00:04:33.600 --> 00:04:35.220
That can be something very dangerous for

00:04:35.220 --> 00:04:38.330
a startup,
to be dependent on the incentive plan.

00:04:38.330 --> 00:04:42.000
And are focusing on
keeping the users engaged

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:45.420
further the dynamics
of the product itself.

00:04:45.420 --> 00:04:46.900
One more thing is that

00:04:47.940 --> 00:04:52.880
incentives can only enhance
the quality of your product.

00:04:52.880 --> 00:04:56.750
It will not replace anything, so if your
product is great, the thing that you're

00:04:56.750 --> 00:05:00.620
doing with incentives is encourage what
you hope that your users will be doing,

00:05:00.620 --> 00:05:04.470
that's the final push,
that's not the main thing.

00:05:04.470 --> 00:05:08.021
You push them to share,
you push them to activate,

